It appears to be impossible to have a Jelly script with text "$\{" in it. For instance:


{code:xml}
<JiraJelly xmlns:jira="jelly:com.atlassian.jira.jelly.JiraTagLib">
   <jira:CreateIssue escapeText="false" project-key="TP" assignee="-1" summary="${" issueKeyVar="issue"/>
</JiraJelly>
{code}

This breaks with:

{quote}Missing '}' character at the end of expression: $\{{quote}

The relevant code is in Jelly's [CompositeExpression class|http://commons.apache.org/jelly/xref/org/apache/commons/jelly/expression/CompositeExpression.html#66]. If it sees "${" it requires a "}". I cannot see any way to disable this expression parsing.

